The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Zimbabwe PM hurt, wife killed
                                                                                                               Zimbabwe PM hurt, wife killed
                            
	Harare, March 7 (Reuters): Zimbabwean Prime Minister Morgan Tsvangirais wife was killed and he was injured yesterday when a truck slammed into their vehicle, officials in his MDC party said.        
	Later today, Tsvangirai left the hospital and was flown to Botswana to recuperate and rest. His face was a little swollen, but otherwise he appeared to be in a stable condition, a Reuters witness said.        
	Tsvangirais wife of 31 years, Susan, was killed in the crash on one of Zimbabwes busiest and most dangerous roads. The leaders MDC party said the car accident could have been avoided if proper security had been put in place.        
	MDC secretary-general and finance minister Tendai Biti said police were examining whether foul play was involved. The driver of the truck, which belongs to the US development agency, is in police custody. The Prime Minister suffered some head and neck wounds.                                                                                                                                                                                     
